            <titre>THE GREAT GATSBY</titre>
            <annee>2014</annee>
            <prix devise="CAD">32</prix>
            <commentaire> I thought that the book was all right. 
                The story was bland for my liking but I did like 
                the social commentary that the book provided, 
                dealing with the issues of their time, alcohol, 
                wealth, and partying. While I do not call this 
                a fun read, I do recommend it be read so that 
                the reader can get a taste of life in the 1920s. 
                The book can be confusing at times and needs to 
                be read carefully or reread to fully understand.
            </commentaire>
